SIMPLE: pricking
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pricking
<hw>Prick"ing</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of piercing
or puncturing with a sharp point.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧There is that speaketh
like the <xex>prickings</xex> of a sword.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Prov. xii. 18
[1583].</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Far.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>The driving of a nail
into a horse's foot so as to produce lameness.</def> <sd>(b)</sd>
<def>Same as <er>Nicking</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A sensation of being pricked.</def>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>The mark or trace left by a hare's foot; a prick;
also, the act of tracing a hare by its footmarks.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <def>Dressing one's self for show; prinking.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pricking-up</ent>⟦br⟧
